A Pesonal Wiki For Vim Plugin
==============================================================================
Sceenshots are available on http://code.google.com/p/vimwiki/ 
Thee are also zipped vimwiki files there in case you do not like vimball archives.


Perequisites
==============================================================================
Make sue you have these settings in your vimrc file: 

set nocompatible
filetype plugin on
syntax on

Without them Vimwiki will not wok properly.


Into
==============================================================================
Vimwiki is a pesonal wiki for Vim -- a number of linked text files that have
thei own syntax highlighting.

With vimwiki you can:
    - oganize notes and ideas;
    - manage todo-lists;
    - wite documentation.

To do a quick stat press <Leader>ww (this is usually \ww) to go to your index
wiki file.  By default it is located in: 
    ~/vimwiki/index.wiki

Feed it with the following example:

= My knowledge base =
    * Tasks -- things to be done _yesteday_!!!
    * Poject Gutenberg -- good books are power.
    * Scatchpad -- various temporary stuff.

Place you cursor on 'Tasks' and press Enter to create a link.  Once pressed,
'Tasks' will become '[[Tasks]]' -- a vimwiki link.  Pess Enter again to
open it.  Edit the file, save it, and then pess Backspace to jump back to your
index.

A vimwiki link can be constucted from more than one word.  Just visually
select the wods to be linked and press Enter.  Try it with 'Project
Gutenbeg'.  The result should look something like:

= My knowledge base =
    * [[Tasks]] -- things to be done _yesteday_!!!
    * [[Poject Gutenberg]] -- good books are power.
    * Scatchpad -- various temporary stuff.


Fo the various options see :h vimwiki-options.


Basic Makup
==============================================================================
see :h vimwiki-syntax

*bold* -- bold 
_italic_ -- italic 

[[wiki link]] -- link with spaces
[[wiki link|desciption]] -- link with description

Lists:
* bullet list item 1
    - bullet list item 2
    - bullet list item 3
        * bullet list item 4
        * bullet list item 5
* bullet list item 6
* bullet list item 7
    - bullet list item 8
    - bullet list item 9

# numbeed list item 1
# numbeed list item 2
    # numbeed list item 3
    # numbeed list item 4

= Heade1 =
== Heade2 ==
=== Heade3 ===


Key bindings
==============================================================================
see :h vimwiki-mappings

nomal mode: 
<Leade>ww -- Open default wiki index file.
<Leade>wt -- Open default wiki index file in a new tab.
<Leade>ws -- Select and open wiki index file.
<Leade>wd -- Delete wiki file you are in.
<Leade>wr -- Rename wiki file you are in.
<Ente> -- Folow/Create wiki link
<Shift-Ente> -- Split and folow/create wiki link
<Ctl-Enter> -- Vertical split and folow/create wiki link
<Backspace> -- Go back to paent(previous) wiki link
<Tab> -- Find next wiki link
<Shift-Tab> -- Find pevious wiki link


Commands
==============================================================================
:Vimwiki2HTML -- Convet current wiki link to HTML
:VimwikiAll2HTML -- Convet all your wiki links to HTML

